text.tspan: Machine with swap available, not swapping
Machine with swap available, currently swapping
• Swap area (no matter the actual size) is reduced to 1/6
• Memory takes up the rest of 5/6
• The maximum physical memory is shown as a number
• The chart shows unavailable (total - available) in blue and available as empty space.
• Cache is considered part of the available (empty area) space.
• Shared is considered part of the used/unavailable space.
• When a machine swaps, it indicates performance issues; swap is red as a warning
